[2026-05-28 23:44:14] local.INFO: Recommendation Step Output {"recommendation":{"confidence":0.8,"customer_explanation":"It looks like you have a water leak under your sink. This means water is escaping from one of the pipes or connections, which can lead to water damage, dampness, and even mold if left untreated. It's important to address this issue soon.","diy_checks":["Carefully look under your sink with a flashlight for any visible drips, wet spots, or puddles. Check the connections where pipes meet, the joints of the P-trap (the U-shaped pipe), and the body of the pipes themselves.","Feel along the pipes and connections with a dry cloth or paper towel to identify where the water is coming from. Sometimes a leak can be very small and only noticeable by touch.","If you have access, gently try to tighten any loose-looking nuts or connections under the sink using an adjustable wrench. Do not overtighten, as this can cause more damage.","Run water in the sink for a few minutes and observe if the leak becomes more apparent or stops after tightening a connection."],"estimated_price_max":3500,"estimated_price_min":1000,"immediate_actions":["Place a bucket or a container directly under the leak to catch any dripping water and prevent further damage to your cabinet or floor.","Try to identify the exact spot of the leak. This will help you or a plumber fix it quickly.","If the leak is significant and you cannot find the shut-off valve under the sink, turn off the main water supply to your house to stop the flow of water and prevent serious damage. The main valve is usually near your water meter or where the main pipe enters your home."],"issue_type":"pipe_leak","likely_cause":"The leak is most likely happening because of a connection that has become loose over time, a rubber washer or seal inside a joint that has worn out, or a small crack in the pipe itself, especially in the 'P-trap' or the drain assembly under the sink.","preventive_maintenance":["Regularly check under your sink for any signs of moisture or leaks. A quick visual inspection every few months can help catch small problems before they become big ones.","Avoid pouring harsh chemical drain cleaners down the sink, as these can corrode pipes and seals over time, leading to leaks.","Ensure that nothing heavy is leaning against or putting pressure on the pipes under the sink, which could cause stress and potential leaks."],"professional_steps":["A plumber will accurately find the source of the leak, which might involve a detailed inspection of all pipes and connections under the sink.","Depending on the cause, they might tighten connections, replace old or damaged washers/seals, repair a cracked pipe using appropriate materials, or replace a damaged section of the pipe, such as the P-trap or a supply line.","They will ensure all connections are properly sealed to prevent future leaks."],"recommended_service":"Leak detection and repair","required_tools":["Bucket","Flashlight","Dry cloths or towels","Adjustable wrench"],"risk_level":"medium","safety_precautions":["Always turn off the water supply to the sink (if a shut-off valve is available) or your whole house before attempting any adjustments or inspections that involve touching the pipes to prevent more water from spilling.","Do not use excessive force when tightening connections, as this can damage threads or crack pipes, making the problem worse.","Wear gloves if you are dealing with dirty water or old pipes.","Never attempt to repair gas lines or electrical components near plumbing; always call a professional for those."],"summary":"You have a leak under your sink, likely from a loose connection, a worn-out part, or a small crack. It needs attention to avoid water damage and mold. You can try some simple checks, but a professional plumber might be needed for a proper fix. The estimated cost for repair is between 1000 and 3500 Nepalese Rupees.","urgency":"medium","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash"}} 
