[2026-05-29 00:06:55] local.INFO: Recommendation Step Output {"recommendation":{"confidence":0.75,"customer_explanation":"You've reported an issue that suggests a plumbing leak, but the exact location or type isn't clear yet. This means water might be escaping from a pipe, fixture, or fitting somewhere in your home or property. Even a small leak can cause significant damage over time if not addressed.","diy_checks":["Carefully check all visible pipes under sinks, behind toilets, and near water heaters for any damp spots, water drips, or discoloration.","Look for puddles or dampness on floors, walls, or ceilings, especially after using water.","Inspect outdoor faucets and garden hoses for leaks when the water is turned on.","If you have an accessible crawl space or basement, check pipes in those areas for moisture or drips. Wear appropriate clothing and use a flashlight.","If you suspect a hidden leak, check your water meter. Note the reading, avoid using any water for an hour or two, and then check the meter again. If the reading has changed, you likely have a hidden leak."],"estimated_price_max":0,"estimated_price_min":0,"immediate_actions":["If you find an active leak, try to locate the main water shut-off valve for your home and turn off the water supply immediately. This will prevent further water damage.","Place a bucket or towels under any visible drips to contain the water.","Do not try to disassemble any pressurized pipes yourself, as this can worsen the leak."],"issue_type":"pipe_leak","likely_cause":"A plumbing leak can be caused by various factors, including aging pipes, loose connections, damaged seals, corroded fittings, or even small cracks due to shifting foundations or minor impacts. Sometimes, extreme weather changes can also stress pipes. Given the general nature of the report, the exact cause needs to be identified through inspection.","preventive_maintenance":["Regularly inspect visible pipes, especially under sinks and around appliances, for any signs of moisture or rust.","Tighten any loose faucet handles or showerheads to prevent minor drips.","If you have outdoor pipes, ensure they are properly insulated to prevent freezing and bursting during cold weather, common in high-altitude areas of Nepal.","Avoid using harsh chemical drain cleaners, as they can corrode pipes over time."],"professional_steps":["If you cannot locate the leak, or if the leak is in a difficult-to-reach area (like behind a wall, under the floor, or underground), it is best to call a licensed plumber.","A plumber will use specialized tools to accurately locate the source of the leak, whether it's visible or hidden.","They will safely repair or replace the damaged pipe or fitting. This might involve cutting into walls or floors, depending on the leak's location.","They can also assess the overall condition of your plumbing system to identify any other potential weak points."],"recommended_service":"General Plumbing Service","required_tools":["Flashlight","Dry cloths or towels","Bucket","Adjustable wrench (for minor tightening of visible connections if safe to do so)"],"risk_level":"medium","safety_precautions":["Always shut off the main water supply before attempting any inspection or repair on active leaks to prevent water damage or personal injury.","Be cautious when inspecting areas that might have electrical components nearby. If water is near electricity, do not touch it and call a professional immediately.","Wear gloves when inspecting drains or potentially dirty areas.","Do not attempt major pipe repairs yourself, especially on pressurized water lines or sewer lines, as improper repairs can lead to larger, more expensive problems or health hazards."],"summary":"You have a suspected plumbing leak. While the exact location is unknown, it carries a medium urgency and risk. First, shut off your main water supply if you find an active leak. Then, perform simple checks with a flashlight and towels to locate the source. If you can't find it or if it's in a wall or difficult spot, call a professional plumber. Prevent future leaks by regularly checking your pipes and insulating outdoor lines. The estimated cost is currently undetermined as it depends entirely on the leak's location and severity.","urgency":"medium","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash"}} 
