[2026-05-29 00:24:59] local.INFO: Recommendation Step Output {"recommendation":{"confidence":0.8,"customer_explanation":"You have a water leak under your sink. This means water is escaping from one of the pipes or connections beneath the basin, potentially causing damage to your cabinets or floor.","diy_checks":["Dry everything under the sink with a cloth and use a flashlight to look for any visible cracks, drips, or wet spots on the pipes, joints, and fittings.","Gently try to tighten any visible nuts or connections by hand. For plastic pipes, be careful not to overtighten. For metal pipes, you can use an adjustable wrench, but be gentle.","If you suspect the leak is from the drain, turn the water supply back on just a little bit and run a small amount of water down the sink while watching closely for drips under the sink. Have a bucket ready."],"estimated_price_max":4500,"estimated_price_min":1500,"immediate_actions":["Shut off the water supply to the sink immediately. Look for the small valves usually located under the sink, on the water supply lines (one for hot, one for cold). Turn them clockwise until they are completely off. If you can't find them or they don't work, you might need to turn off the main water supply to your house.","Place a bucket or basin directly under the leak and use towels or old cloths to soak up any standing water to prevent further damage to your cabinets or floor."],"issue_type":"pipe_leak","likely_cause":"Over time, pipes, joints, and seals can wear out, crack, or become loose. Common reasons for a leak under the sink include loose connections at the P-trap (the U-shaped pipe), issues with the water supply lines (hot or cold water pipes), or a crack in the drain pipe itself.","preventive_maintenance":["Regularly check under your sinks for any signs of moisture, water stains, or a musty smell, especially after heavy use.","Avoid pouring harsh chemicals down your drain, as they can corrode pipes and seals over time, leading to leaks.","Be gentle when using the sink, especially with heavy items, to avoid putting strain on the drain assembly and pipes.","If you notice any slow drainage, address it promptly to prevent clogs that can put pressure on pipes and connections."],"professional_steps":["You should call a licensed plumber if you can't find the exact source of the leak after your initial checks, or if tightening connections doesn't stop the leak.","A plumber is needed if the leak is from a major pipe or connection, not just a simple drain fitting, or if you don't feel comfortable performing the checks yourself.","The plumber will accurately identify the leak source, which could be a worn washer, a cracked pipe section, or a loose joint, and will then repair or replace the affected parts. This might involve using specialized tools to access tight spaces or cutting and joining new pipe sections."],"recommended_service":"Pipe leak inspection and repair","required_tools":["Bucket","Towels or rags","Flashlight","Adjustable wrench","Screwdriver (to open cabinet panels if needed)"],"risk_level":"medium","safety_precautions":["Always shut off the water supply before attempting any inspection or repair to prevent accidental flooding.","Do not use strong chemical drain cleaners, as they can damage pipes, especially plastic ones, and are hazardous to your health and plumbing.","Wear gloves if you need to touch dirty drain pipes.","Avoid disassembling pressurized water supply pipes unless you are absolutely sure the main water supply is off and you are confident in your abilities."],"summary":"You have a medium urgency pipe leak under your sink. Your first step should be to shut off the water and clean up any spills. Then, safely inspect the pipes and connections with basic tools. If you can't find or fix the leak, or if it seems like a bigger issue, it's best to call a professional plumber. Regular checks and mindful use can help prevent future leaks. The estimated cost for professional repair in Nepal is between NPR 1500 and NPR 4500.","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash"}} 
